There is still a big gap in the supplies of the first-line medical staff in Wuhan. On February 11,2020, the health and Family Planning Publicity and education center of Hubei Province announced the acceptance of social donations by hospitals in Wuhan through the official wechat account "healthy Hubei" .

Interface news comb discovery, including Wuhan First Hospital, Wuhan Central Hospital, Wuhan University affiliated Colleague Hospital, Wuhan Fourth Hospital, Wuhan Fifth Hospital, Wuhan Golden Pool Hospital, Wuhan Children's hospital more than 20 hospitals, all in "healthy Hubei" the announcement which releases Wuhan each big hospital accepts the society donation.

These Wuhan hospitals that have issued public announcements on accepting donations from the public, the missing materials mainly include medical protective mask, goggles, protective clothing, mobile ultraviolet disinfection vehicle, mobile air disinfection machine, long shoe covers, medical caps, surgical clothes and other medical protective materials. Each hospital has marked the quality requirements of the missing materials or the standards at home and abroad.

In fact, starting from late January, many hospitals in Wuhan and many provinces and cities across the country have experienced a shortage of medical protection materials, and have issued announcements to accept donations from society.

According to a report by Xinhua News Agency on February 8, there is still a shortage of medical materials in Wuhan. On February 6, for example, the demand for medical protective clothing in Wuhan was 59,900 pieces, with a gap of 41,400 pieces The demand for N95 masks for medical use was 119,000, with a shortfall of 56,800; the demand for goggles and masks was 22,500, with a shortfall of 19,200.

Wuhan First Hospital staff told the interface news, the hospital is mainly short of N95 masks, protective clothing, medical surgical masks and other medical protection materials. On February 10th, the Charity Donation Bulletin was updated to the fourth edition, and the College has previously received three donations from the public.

"after receiving donations from society, it has solved a lot of problems for us, but N95 masks and protective clothing are still in short supply, because the standards of such protective materials are quite strict, and the standards of some donated materials may not meet the requirements, so we still hope to get some help from society for these protective materials, " the official said.

Wuhan Children's Hospital has updated the notice to the fifth edition of the medical protection materials. "At present, we are short of protective clothing and medical protective masks. We are short of about 10,000 sets of protective clothing and about 50,000 medical protective masks, " said a staff member at Wuhan Children's Hospital.

Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital has also issued a notice to accept donations. In short supply of protective materials, such as surgical masks, N95 masks, disposable masks, protective clothing, disposable surgical clothes, etc. . A staff member of the hospital said that the hospital is also in short supply of ECG monitors, breathing machines and other equipment. "With more and more patients admitted to our hospital, there is still a shortage of ECG monitors and many patients need to use suction machines, " he said.

According to reports from Kwangmyong, on February 10, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China released news that since the outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia, Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China Medical Supply Enterprises have resumed work and expanded production, will work with relevant departments to do a good job in medical supplies, focusing on Wuhan and Hubei Province medical supplies allocation work.

The report said that as of 2400 hours on February 9, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology had allocated 470,100 pieces of National Standard Medical Protective Clothing, and organized the distribution of 357,800 medical isolation eye masks / medical isolation masks, 84 disinfectants, 64,500 boxes and 31.25 tons of hands-free disinfectants, 663 automatic infrared thermometers for use in Wuhan and Hubei Province.

On the evening of February 10, the National Health Commission coordinated 19 provinces to support Hubei Province in addition to 16 cities and counties in Wuhan, and confirmed the relationship between the counterpart support. At the same time, the supporting provinces should strengthen communication and docking with the recipient cities, actively coordinate the support needed masks, protective clothing, goggles and other related medical protective items.
